headline: $340M refinancing secured for 50 & 70 Columbus in Jersey City
summary: JLL's Capital Markets group, in conjunction with BlueGate Partners LLC, announced today that it has arranged a $340 million refinancing for 50 & 70 Columbus, a 938-unit mixed-use property located in Jersey City, New Jersey.

headline: More like the Mag 800: Strategist talks AI concentration risks
summary: Software developer Oracle (ORCL) continues to see its stock skyrocket this morning after posting powerful fiscal first quarter earnings after Tuesday's market close. Truist Chief Investment Officer and chief market strategist Keith Lerner expands upon concentration risk concerns pertaining to the growing AI industry and artificial intelligence products offered by more large-cap tech companies. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.

headline: Truist names veteran leaders to Commercial and Corporate Banking roles
summary: Truist Financial Corporation (NYSE: TFC) today announced Jenna Kelly as head of the Consumer and Retail practice group within Truist Corporate Banking and Travis Rhodes as North Carolina West regional president for Truist's Commercial Banking business.
